title: Google\Cloud\Dataproc\V1\JobReference
name: JobReference
description:
Encapsulates the full scoping used to reference a job.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.dataproc.v1.JobReference

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.project_id
params.description: Required. The ID of the Google Cloud Platform project that the job belongs to.

params.name: data.job_id
params.description: Optional. The job ID, which must be unique within the project. The job ID is generated by the server upon job submission or provided by the user as a means to perform retries without creating duplicate jobs. The ID must contain only letters (a-z, A-Z), numbers (0-9), underscores (_), or hyphens (-). The maximum length is 100 characters.
